  "solution": {
    "approach": "For each test case we only need to check two conditions: whether b > a + c and whether b is odd. Both checks are O(1). We read the input, evaluate the boolean expression (b > a + c && b % 2 == 1) and output 1 for true, 0 for false. The algorithm runs in linear time with respect to T and uses O(1) extra space.",
    "timeComplexity": "O(T) overall, O(1) per test case.",
    "spaceComplexity": "O(1) besides the input storage.",
    "code": {
      "C": "",
      "C++": "",
      "Java": "import java.io.*;\nimport java.util.*;\n\npublic class Main {\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n        int T = Integer.parseInt(br.readLine().trim());\n        for (int t = 0; t < T; t++) {\n            StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(br.readLine());\n            int a = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());\n            int b = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());\n            int c = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());\n            int res = (b > a + c && (b & 1) == 1) ? 1 : 0;\n            sb.append(res);\n            if (t + 1 < T) sb.append('\\n');\n        }\n        System.out.print(sb.toString());\n    }\n}",
      "Python3": "",
      "JavaScript": ""
    }
  },
